# Fair and Unbiased Assessment System

## Project Overview
The **Fair and Unbiased Assessment System** is an AI-based academic assessment and report generation system designed for universities and educational institutions. The system automates assessment management, evaluation workflows, and academic reporting while reducing manual effort and grading bias.

Students can submit assessments digitally, faculty members can manage courses and evaluations, and the system can generate AI-assisted academic performance reports.

This project focuses on:
- Academic workflow management
- Assessment and evaluation automation
- Database design and normalization
- Enrollment and teaching assignment management
- AI-based report generation

---

## Features

- User authentication and management
- Student and faculty management
- Department and program management
- Batch, semester, session, and section handling
- Course and teaching assignment management
- Student enrollment management
- Assessment creation and tracking
- Student submission handling
- AI-generated evaluation processing
- Student and class performance reports
- Historical academic record management
- Activity logging and monitoring

---

## System Modules

### User Management
Handles authentication and role-based access for students and faculty members.

### Academic Management
Manages departments, programs, batches, semesters, sessions, sections, and courses.

### Enrollment Management
Maintains student enrollment history and repeat-course handling.

### Assessment Management
Allows faculty members to create and manage assessments.

### Submission & Evaluation
Stores student submissions and AI-generated evaluation results.

### Report Generation
Generates:
- Student reports
- Class performance reports
- AI-generated evaluation summaries

