---

## Database Design Highlights

The database system is designed using:
- ERD/EERD modeling
- Normalization techniques
- Supertype/Subtype relationships
- Associative entities
- Proper cardinalities and participation constraints

### Main Entities
- User
- Student
- Faculty
- Department
- Program
- Batch
- Semester
- Session
- Section
- Course
- Teacher_Assignment
- Enrollment
- Assessment
- Submission
- Evaluation

---

## Business Objectives

- Reduce bias in academic assessment
- Automate evaluation workflows
- Improve academic data management
- Maintain historical academic records
- Support scalable university workflows
- Generate automated reports

